CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, September 17, 1966, pg. 4B reads: "Moonlight Cruise- Members of the Cubadettes Club of Pittsburgh, recently sponsored a gala Moonlight cruise on the Gateway Clipper.  Among those enjoying the affair were Mr. and Mrs. Charles Gilbert, Mrs. Hazel White, Joseph Williams and Mrs. Martha Gilbert of New York City, houseguests of Mr. and Mrs. Lou Turner of Wilkinsburg Ave., Pittsburgh.  Others on the boat ride were: James O. Percy, Ann Banks, Addie Chandler, Lucille Harris, Mr. and Mrs. Luscious Yates, Mrs. Ted Anderson, Mr. and Mrs. George Jackson, all pictured on the top deck of the boat.  Not pictured were Mr. and Mrs. Edward Jeffries, Ted Anderson and Frank McKinney."
TitMainTitle: Group of men and women, including members from the Cubadettes Club of Pittsburgh, standing on deck of Gateway Clipper riverboat for a Moonlight Cruise
